=9CRight now, I=E2=80=99m trying to figure out just getting stuff cleaned u=
p here,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CBut the question for me is, at 66, where=
 do I want to spend the next four to eight years?
Where can I make the biggest difference, the most impact? To be helpful? Th=
ere=E2=80=99s no secret I love public service. I served under three mayors.=
 I loved it. Obviously, I ran for mayor, but I=E2=80=99m not seeking to be =
a politician. I=E2=80=99m seeking to find a path that allows me to do some =
really good things, whether that is in the mayor=E2=80=99s office or the go=
