x;">Even if the governorship is the larger prize, Caruso clearly holds more
<em>personal</em> animus for Bass. He told me that Bass shot him a text whe=
n he announced Steadfast LA last week: <em>Happy to work with you. </em>Oth=
erwise, the two rivals have not been in contact. That=E2=80=99s probably no=
t a surprise, given that Caruso has been spraying Bass with <strong>Kendric=
k Lamar</strong> levels of haterade since the January firestorms, when Bass=
 was overseas, having departed for Ghana even after receiving warnings of d=
angerously dry fire conditions in Los Angeles. Since
returning=E2=80=94after the Palisades was mostly destroyed=E2=80=94she has =
faced blistering criticism for a lack of leadership and clear communication=
=2E <strong>Ari Emanuel</strong>, one o=
f her most prominent supporters in the=
 mayor=E2=80=99s race against Caruso, told me that Bass=E2=80=99s decision =
to leave the country was =E2=80=9Ca dereliction of duty.=E2=80=9D Even <em>=
The New York Times</em> noted this week that Gov. <strong>Gavin Newsom</str=
ong> =E2=80=9Coften has seemed a more visible figure than Ms. Bass=E2=80=9D=
 during the cleanup effort. =E2=80=9CThe city
is lost,=E2=80=9D Caruso told me. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s like a black hole o=
ver there. Nobody knows what other people are doing. I put in a call to the=
 mayor. She hasn=E2=80=99t called me back. =E2=80=A6 The county and the sta=
te have actually been good. Gavin, in particular, has been great. He came t=
o my office. He took notes. He was asking a lot of great questions. He has =
been very responsive.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Meanwhile, Caruso=E2=80=
=99s commentary drips with contempt
for Bass. =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m not trying to throw her under the bus, but p=
eople need to see leadership and that things are actually tangibly happenin=
g,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CThe frustration level is at an all-time high.=
 There aren=E2=80=99t a lot of answers out there. There=E2=80=99s no schedu=
le. How could there not be a schedule after four weeks!=E2=80=9D I asked Ca=
ruso whether his dialed-up criticisms=E2=80=94which began the first night o=
f the fires, when he called up Fox 11=E2=80=99s <strong>Elex Michaelson </s=
trong>and ripped Bass for being an absentee
mayor=E2=80=94were hindering her ability to lead. =E2=80=9CShould I maybe s=
top criticizing her? Criticizing her leadership?=E2=80=9D he asked. =E2=80=
=9CI guess what happens is, they keep stepping in stuff.=E2=80=9D</p><p sty=
le=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bo=
ttom:0px;">Caruso pointed to the recent scandal involving <strong>Steve Sob=
oroff</strong>, the former Los Angeles Police Commissioner whom Bass appoin=
ted as her =E2=80=9Crecovery czar.=E2=80=9D Somehow even that became a cont=
roversy: Bass approved a $500,000
salary for Soboroff to be doled out over three months, funded by charitable=
 organizations that haven=E2=80=99t been named=E2=80=94her latest in a casc=
ade of unforced political errors. Soboroff said his expertise was worth the=
 price, but he and Bass were forced to backpedal after a predictable public=
 retaliation. (Soboroff will now work for free.) =E2=80=9CYou=E2=80=99ve go=
t to be kidding me!=E2=80=9D Caruso exclaimed. =E2=80=9CYou can=E2=80=99t e=
ven manage one consultant=E2=80=99s contract, but you=E2=80=99re in charge =
of managing the second-largest city in the
country? I=E2=80=99m sorry, I find that to just be so damn frustrating.=E2=
=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin:0;">From my conversations with strategists around the state and people=
 close to Caruso, making a second bid for mayor seems more likely than one =
for governor. Even so, he=E2=80=99d have a steep hill to climb. Yes, Los An=
geles has plenty of independents and Republicans out in the Valley, and pro=
bably some new ones in the Palisades. But L.A. remains Democratic to its co=
re=E2=80=94a
city so progressive that it voted for <strong>Bernie Sanders </strong>over =
Joe Biden in the 2020 presidential primary.</p></div>
